class CardSet Position information of the display on a diagram of all classes and of their associations

CardSet 1 -- * Card
A Card has A CardSet. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one CardSet.
A CardSet has some Cards. It can have none, and there is no upper bound defined.
When a Card is created, its CardSet must be assigned. When a Card is deleted, its CardSet is not deleted and its list of Cards is decreased. When a CardSet is deleted, its Cards are not deleted. They are assigned to another CardSet.
